race.comment: LOOK HERE (7) travelled handy and wouldn't lie down when beaten under a length over this course and distance two back. Failed in town last time but back here back to this level she makes plenty of appeal. ERNAUX (5) resumes. Raced well in town at all three appearances last prep. Two recent trials should have her forward enough to emulate the efforts of the last campaign. BEVERLY HILLS (9) drops back in grade after being well beaten at Rosehill on resuming. Will at least be fitter for the run. Aside from that last start blemish, all other public outings have been most encouraging. SARA'S ROCKET (3) battled on well enough on debut at Newcastle. Will have taken valuable race experience and fitness from the run.
